Installation Instructions
=========================

Make
----

QuerySort uses make. To build and install querysort,  simply run 'make' and then
'make install'  as root.  On Linux,  you also  need to  run  'ldconfig'  as root
afterwards in order to update the shared library cache.

The QuerySort command line  uses liburiparser for URI validation,  and uriparser
development package is required at build time.

RPM
---

QuerySort  can also be  built as  RPM packages,  simply run 'make rpm'  and then
'rpm -i' or your favorite RPM-based package manager as root.

